OL,3,C'Infected blood victim compensation
OL,4,Cfulfils vow I made 10 years ago' ` Hunt
OL,6,FAfter telling his family the news that
OL,7,Fhe only had months to live, he visited
OL,8,Fthe then health secretary, Mr Hunt, in
OL,9,FWhitehall.
OL,11,FHe told the future Chancellor he was
OL,12,Fangry that infected patients and their
OL,13,Ffamilies had not received a full and
OL,14,Ffair settlement.
OL,16,FTowards the end of the meeting, Mr
OL,17,FHunt shook his hand and said: "Don't
OL,18,Fworry about this, we'll sort it."
OL,20,FJust a few months later, Mr Dorricott
OL,21,Fdied, aged just 47.
